card.question:
Even for a simple TXT card, styling is possible - to overwrite the |___| definition, set the following style:

  div.qa-txt {
    font-family: sans-serif;
  }

card.answer:
monospace
The <div>'s for displaying the question and answer of the card use the (CSS) class "qa-txt", which is defined in ms.css as follows:
  div.qa-txt {
    width: 98%;
    padding: 0.5ex 0.2ex 0.5ex 0.2ex;
    margin: 0.3ex auto 0.3ex auto;
    border-width: 1px;
    border-style: solid;
    border-radius: 0.3ex;
    border-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, .25);
    min-height: 2.5em;
    font-family: monospace;
    white-space: pre-wrap;
    overflow-wrap: break-word;
  }
